<topic id="topic_vcr_ty4_44">
  <title>cursor.explain()</title>
  <body>
    <section>
      <title>NAME</title>
      <p>explain - Return the access plan of the current cursor.</p>
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>SYNOPSIS</title>
      <p></p><apiname>cousor.explain</apiname>()
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>CATEGORY</title>
      <p></p>Cursor
    </section>
    <section>
      <title>DESCRIPTION</title> 
      <p>Return the access plan of the current cursor.</p>
      <parml>
        <plentry>
          <pt>FullName (string)</pt>
          <pd>Collection Name.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>ScanType (string)</pt>
          <pd>Scanning Type: TableScan: "TBSCAN"; IndexScan:"IXSCAN"
          </pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>IdxName (string)</pt>
          <pd>Index name.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>UseExtSort (bool)</pt>
          <pd>Whether use external sort or not.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>Node (string)</pt>
          <pd>Node Name.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>ReturnNum (int64)</pt>
          <pd>Number of returned records.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>ElapsedTime (float64)</pt>
          <pd>Elapsed Time(seconds).</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>IdxRead (int64)</pt>
          <pd>Number of Index read.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>DataRead (int64)</pt>
          <pd>Number of data read.</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>UsrCpu (float64)</pt>
          <pd>Time used by cpu in user mode(seconds).</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>SysCpu (float64)</pt>
          <pd>Time used by cpu in kernel mode(seconds).</pd>
        </plentry>
        <plentry>
          <pt>SubCollections (Json Array)</pt>
          <pd>The access plan of each sub-collections of the vertical-partitioning collection.</pd>
        </plentry>
      </parml>
      <note>
        <ul><li>If the collection is splitted into different replica groups, each replica group will return its own access plan correspondingly.</li>          
        </ul></note>      
    </section>    
    <section>
      <title>Examples</title>
      <p>Suppose foo.bar is a horizontal-partitioning collection splitted in three replica groups.</p>
      <codeblock>db.foo.bar.find().sort({b:1}).explain()</codeblock>
      <p>Return:</p>
      <codeblock>{
  "FullName": "foo.bar",
  "ScanType": "TBSCAN",
  "IdxName": "",
  "UseExtSort": true,
  "Node": "vmsvr2-cent-x64:40020",
  "ReturnNum": 38,
  "ElapsedTime": 0.000477,
  "IdxRead": 0,
  "DataRead": 38,
  "UsrCpu": 0,
  "SysCpu": 0
}
{
  "FullName": "foo.bar",
  "ScanType": "TBSCAN",
  "IdxName": "",
  "UseExtSort": true,
  "Node": "vmsvr2-cent-x64:40000",
  "ReturnNum": 34,
  " ElapsedTime ": 0.000415,
  "IdxRead": 0,
  "DataRead": 34,
  "UsrCpu": 0,
  "SysCpu": 0
}
{
  "FullName": "foo.bar",
  "ScanType": "TBSCAN",
  "IdxName": "",
  "UseExtSort": true,
  "Node": "vmsvr2-cent-x64:40010",
  "ReturnNum": 28,
  " ElapsedTime ": 0.000517,
  "IdxRead": 0,
  "DataRead": 28,
  "UsrCpu": 0,
  "SysCpu": 0
}</codeblock>
    </section>
